comment:
* Information about a call that is used between InCallService and Telecom.
 * @hide

variables.name: CREATOR
variables.comment: Responsible for creating ParcelableCall objects for deserialized Parcels.

methods.name: public String getId()
methods.comment: The unique ID of the call.

methods.name: public int getState()
methods.comment: The current state of the call.

methods.name: public DisconnectCause getDisconnectCause()
methods.comment:
* Reason for disconnection, as described by {@link android.telecomm.DisconnectCause}. Valid
     * when call state is {@link CallState#DISCONNECTED}.

methods.name: public List<String> getCannedSmsResponses()
methods.comment: * The set of possible text message responses when this call is incoming.

methods.name: public int getCapabilities()
methods.comment: Bit mask of actions a call supports, values are defined in {@link CallCapabilities}.

methods.name: public int getProperties()
methods.comment: Bitmask of properties of the call.

methods.name: public int getSupportedAudioRoutes()
methods.comment: Bitmask of supported routes of the call

methods.name: public long getConnectTimeMillis()
methods.comment: The time that the call switched to the active state.

methods.name: public Uri getHandle()
methods.comment: The endpoint to which the call is connected.

methods.name: public int getHandlePresentation()
methods.comment: * The presentation requirements for the handle. See {@link TelecomManager} for valid values.

methods.name: public String getCallerDisplayName()
methods.comment: The endpoint to which the call is connected.

methods.name: public int getCallerDisplayNamePresentation()
methods.comment:
* The presentation requirements for the caller display name.
     * See {@link TelecomManager} for valid values.

methods.name: public GatewayInfo getGatewayInfo()
methods.comment: Gateway information for the call.

methods.name: public PhoneAccountHandle getAccountHandle()
methods.comment: PhoneAccountHandle information for the call.

methods.name: public VideoCallImpl getVideoCallImpl(String callingPackageName, int targetSdkVersion)
methods.comment:
* Returns an object for remotely communicating through the video call provider's binder.
     *
     * @param callingPackageName the package name of the calling InCallService.
     * @param targetSdkVersion the target SDK version of the calling InCallService.
     * @return The video call.

methods.name: public ParcelableRttCall getParcelableRttCall()
methods.comment:
* RTT communication channel information
     * @return The ParcelableRttCall

methods.name: public String getParentCallId()
methods.comment: * The conference call to which this call is conferenced. Null if not conferenced.

methods.name: public List<String> getChildCallIds()
methods.comment:
* The child call-IDs if this call is a conference call. Returns an empty list if this is not
     * a conference call or if the conference call contains no children.

methods.name: public StatusHints getStatusHints()
methods.comment:
* The status label and icon.
     *
     * @return Status hints.

methods.name: public int getVideoState()
methods.comment:
* The video state.
     * @return The video state of the call.

methods.name: public Bundle getExtras()
methods.comment:
* Any extras associated with this call.
     *
     * @return a bundle of extras

methods.name: public Bundle getIntentExtras()
methods.comment:
* Extras passed in as part of the original call intent.
     *
     * @return The intent extras.

methods.name: public boolean isVideoCallProviderChanged()
methods.comment:
* Indicates to the receiver of the {@link ParcelableCall} whether a change has occurred in the
     * {@link android.telecom.InCallService.VideoCall} associated with this call.  Since
     * {@link #getVideoCall()} creates a new {@link VideoCallImpl}, it is useful to know whether
     * the provider has changed (which can influence whether it is accessed).
     *
     * @return {@code true} if the video call changed, {@code false} otherwise.

methods.name: public long getCreationTimeMillis()
methods.comment: * @return The time the call was created, in milliseconds since the epoch.

methods.name: public int getCallDirection()
methods.comment: * Indicates whether the call is an incoming or outgoing call.

methods.name: public int getCallerNumberVerificationStatus()
methods.comment:
* Gets the verification status for the phone number of an incoming call as identified in
     * ATIS-1000082.
     * @return the verification status.

methods.name: public String getContactDisplayName()
methods.comment: * @return the name of the remote party as derived from a contacts DB lookup.

methods.name: public String getActiveChildCallId()
methods.comment:
* @return On a CDMA conference with two participants, returns the ID of the child call that's
     *         currently active.

methods.name: public int describeContents()
methods.comment: {@inheritDoc}

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel destination, int flags)
methods.comment: Writes ParcelableCall object into a Parcel.

methodNames: public VideoCallImpl getVideoCallImpl(String callingPackageName, int targetSdkVersion)
public void writeToParcel(Parcel destination, int flags)
